        "formula": "Let x be the input tensor of shape (N, C_in, H_in, W_in) with N=8, C_in=64, H_in=1024, W_in=1024. Let weight be the weight tensor of shape (C_in, C_out, kernel_size, kernel_size) with C_out=64, kernel_size=3. The transposed convolution uses stride=1, padding=0, output_padding=0, dilation=1. The output tensor y has shape (N, C_out, H_out, W_out) where H_out = (H_in - 1) * stride - 2 * padding + dilation * (kernel_size - 1) + output_padding + 1 = 1026, W_out = 1026 similarly. For n in [0, N-1], oc in [0, C_out-1], h in [0, H_out-1], w in [0, W_out-1]: y[n, oc, h, w] = sum_{ic=0}^{C_in-1} sum_{kh=0}^{kernel_size-1} sum_{kw=0}^{kernel_size-1} weight[ic, oc, kh, kw] * x[n, ic, h - kh, w - kw], where x[n, ic, h - kh, w - kw] is treated as 0 when h - kh < 0 or >= H_in or w - kw < 0 or >= W_in.",
        "boundary_treatment": "Zero padding is implicitly applied on the input boundaries. When the mapped input index (h-kh, w-kw) falls outside the valid input range [0, H_in-1] x [0, W_in-1], the corresponding x value is zero. No explicit padding of the input tensor. The output spatial size is computed as given by the formula. Since groups=1, all input channels contribute to all output channels. No output cropping or other boundary handling is performed.",
